abstract: AUSTIN, Tex., Sept. 2 (UPI)--The editor of the University of Texas student newspaper was jailed briefly on contempt of court charges today for refusing to give up photographs of a campus protest that resulted in criminal charges against some Iranians.
headline_main: A Student Editor Is Jailed in Texas In Iranians' Trial; Serves Briefly for Refusal to Give Photos to Court Trial of 16 Continues
headline_print_headline: A Student Editor Is Jailed in Texas In Iranians' Trial; Serves Briefly for Refusal to Give Photos to Court Trial of 16 Continues

abstract: Senator Donald W. Stewart led yesterday in Alabama's Democratic primary, but the son of a former governor was close to forcing him into a runoff election for the party's Senate nomination.

abstract: TAKE a native son of Colorado. Train him as a lawyer. Give him a Brooklyn-born wife, and let her have a Ph.D. in sociology from Princeton.  So that he won't be too outclassed, give him an M.A. in sociology himself. Plunk the two of them down for a year in a vast empty Colorado farm county: 2,500 square miles, 6,500 people.
WHEN he damaged a knee on a punt return for the New York Jets in 1973, an injury that would require surgery, he  had been awake on cocaine for three days in the past week.

abstract: READING "Changing of the Guard" by DavidBroder is like eavesdropping on the conversations of people who wonder why they are so  successful when the system still doesn't seem to be working. Always the last to know, they barely suspect that they may be the problem to which they seek a solution.

BALTIMORE, Aug. 30 (AP)--Rick Miller drove in four runs and Jason Thompson rapped a three-run pinch-hit home run to lead the California Angels to a 12-6 victory over the slumping Baltimore Orioles tonight.
